          "notes": "Module excels in narrative framing, concept accuracy, and content calibration—the opening case studies and expert citations create genuine stake and the four-lesson progression builds coherently. However, D5 (Applied Outcome) critically underperforms: the labs are conversational AI assistants without clear task completion criteria, success metrics, or executability validation; quiz questions test recall of facts rather than judgment about real design tradeoffs; and learners lack a concrete new capability (e.g., actually conducting a harm audit, redesigning a feature, or evaluating an AI system's vulnerability profile). The module teaches addiction mechanics brilliantly but leaves learners unable to apply this knowledge.",
